    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-black-bean-tofu-and-pak-choi-with-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice </strong>to<strong> </strong>an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>with<strong> </strong>300ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cover tightly with<strong> tin foil </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>baked\u00a0rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-black-bean-tofu-and-pak-choi-with-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Wash your <strong>pak choi </strong>and slice in half lengthways, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-black-bean-tofu-and-pak-choi-with-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based,<strong> hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, drain your <strong>tofu</strong> and crumble it into large chunks with your fingers directly into the dish</p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-black-bean-tofu-and-pak-choi-with-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once brown, add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>black bean paste </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) then cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong>, a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>to the dish</p><p>Give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-black-bean-tofu-and-pak-choi-with-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then put the dish in the oven, uncovered, for and initial 15 min</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-black-bean-tofu-and-pak-choi-with-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tofu has had 15 min, top the dish with the <strong>pak choi halves</strong></p><p>Return the dish to the oven, covered, for a further 10 min or until the veg is tender \u2013 this is your <strong>oven baked spicy black bean tofu & pak choi</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-black-bean-tofu-and-pak-choi-with-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> oven baked spicy black bean tofu & pak choi </strong>with the<strong> baked\u00a0rice</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
